page.title: 14LOCAL HISTORY
page.content: {HISTORY { In the area there is a village that contains an old water mill. It is not used any more. The mill has four floors which still contain a lot of machinery. Trunkwell House was built in the 17th century. It got its name from its first owner and it has twenty rooms 5 of them are large bedrooms. Beech Hill House was built in the 1720s by the Harrison family. It has a large cellar which covers the floorspace of the house. There is also a secret passage way in the house. There are some old kennels that are 300 years old. They are still in use housing dogs that belong to the Duke of Wellington. There is a 20ft well that is 200 years old.
